<section class="sect" id="problem">
  <div class="wrap">

    <p class="sect-eyebrow" data-reveal>The Problem</p>
    <h2 class="sect-heading" data-reveal>Ruby package management still feels like startup tax.</h2>
    <p class="sect-body" data-reveal>
      Rails teams pay for the same friction over and over:
      cold CLI startup, Bundler overhead, container path mismatch, and dependency tooling that feels split across three eras.
    </p>

    <div class="symptoms" data-stagger>
      <div class="symptom">
        <p class="symptom-name">Slow path to first feedback</p>
        <p class="symptom-desc">Parsing, bootstrapping, and basic gem tasks start with Ruby process cost before useful work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="symptom">
        <p class="symptom-name">Rails workflow fragmentation</p>
        <p class="symptom-desc">`gem`, Bundler, project tasks, and Rails commands all feel related, but they do not live in one coherent CLI.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="symptom">
        <p class="symptom-name">CI and Docker churn</p>
        <p class="symptom-desc">Environment-specific paths and repeated install work keep slowing down container builds and deploy flows.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="symptom">
        <p class="symptom-name">Poor observability</p>
        <p class="symptom-desc">When dependencies drift or lockfiles get heavy, the default toolchain rarely explains the problem quickly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sect {
    padding: var(--sp-24) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .sect-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .sect-heading {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 4vw, var(--text-3xl));
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }

  .sect-body {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .symptoms {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .symptom {
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .symptom:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
  .symptom:nth-child(3), .symptom:nth-child(4) { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }

  .symptom-name {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .symptom-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .symptoms { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .symptom { border-right: none; }
  }
</style>
